  "prompt": "I am interested in a girl but she wants to just be friends. What do I do?",
  "response": "Navigating feelings for someone who prefers to remain friends can be challenging, but it's important to approach the situation with respect for her feelings and boundaries. Here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. **Respect Her Wishes**: Acknowledge her desire to keep things platonic. It\u2019s crucial to respect her feelings, as pushing for more can damage the friendship.\n\n2. **Evaluate Your Feelings**: Take some time to reflect on your feelings. Are you okay with just being friends? Sometimes, spending time together without romantic expectations can be fulfilling.\n\n3. **Communicate Openly**: If you feel comfortable, consider having an open conversation with her. You might express how you feel but also emphasize that you value her friendship and want to respect her wishes.\n\n4. **Create Boundaries**: If being just friends is too difficult for you right now, it might be helpful to establish some boundaries. This could mean taking some space to process your feelings.\n\n5. **Focus on Yourself**: Invest time in hobbies, friendships, and interests that make you happy. This can help you gain perspective and may also help you move on if that becomes necessary.\n\n6. **Be Kind**: Regardless of the outcome, be kind and supportive. The friendship can still be valuable in its own right.\n\n7. **Stay Open to New Connections**: While maintaining your existing friendships, remain open to meeting new people. This can help diversify your social connections and potentially lead you to someone who reciprocates your romantic interests.\n\nUltimately, mutual respect and understanding are key. Whatever happens, it's important to prioritize healthy communication and emotional well-being.",
